Rating: 4
This was delicious! I made some adjustments... I served it with spinach instead of mixed greens. I also toasted the baguettes a bit before spreading on the goat cheese and cut the pieces up smaller so they were more like croutons instead of crostini. I chopped up the sundried tomatoes and let them marinade in the dressing for a couple of hours so it was more like a homemade sundried tomato dressing. I added a pinch of salt and pepper to the dressing. But here was the real kicker... I topped the salad with caramelized onion! Served this at a brunch and it went in minutes.

Rating: 4
Made it the first time using a smoked goat cheese and it was fantastic. I think the quality of the cheese definitely makes a difference, but as other reviews say this is a simple and delicious dish to make.

