Rating: 4
YUM! YUM! YUM! This was so simple but so delicous. I served it as an appetizer and it was to die for. The goat cheese in combination with the vinegar, garlic and oil was just fantastic. I recommend this to anyone who wants to impress their guests with out too much effort. Really, really good!!

Rating: 4
This was a great appetizer!! For a great variation, I added fresh basil on top of the crostini after they came out of the oven.

Rating: 4
This was a wonderful salad! Given that field greens now come in convenient bags, it is very easy to make. I toasted the pine nuts on the stove in some butter, which added both flavor and crunch. Anyone who loves goat cheese should try this.

Rating: 4
Excellent! I didn't have pinenuts so I used toasted almond slices. I omitted the sundried tomatoes and used 1 Tbsp. balsamic vinegar and 1 Tbsp. red wine vinegar. The crostini were a nice touch.